      • getOwner

        public Element getOwner()
        Each element can be owned by some other element. When an owner is deleted, it deletes all objects owned by it. A box's owner is a container (or one of its derived classes â€” another box or diagram), a line is owned by a container. A label is owned by a box, a line, a label or a container. Container's owner is a container. A diagram is not owned by any other element.
        Returns:
        the owner of this object, or possibly null, if this element is a diagram.

        public final Diagram getDiagram()

      • remove

        public void remove()
        Removes the element and its descendant elements. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction.

      • remove

        public void remove(boolean adjust)
        Removes the element and its descendant elements. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction if adjust is set to true.
        Parameters:
        adjust - whether to adjust the diagram after the element removal
